WEBVTT

00:01.369 --> 00:03.502
<i> Previously on "nashville"...</i>
I'm gay.

00:03.504 --> 00:05.504
I'm gonna have to drop you
from the label.

00:05.506 --> 00:06.939
Is this you
we're listening to?

00:06.941 --> 00:08.941
Did it all independently.
Really?

00:08.943 --> 00:10.809
Let's hear it
for the owner of the beverly,

00:10.811 --> 00:13.946
Mr. Deacon claybourne!

00:13.948 --> 00:15.981
Juliette has to
prove herself.

00:15.983 --> 00:17.616
Okay. I agree
to supervised visits.

00:17.618 --> 00:18.784
Deacon:
We<i> are</i> trying to help her,

00:18.786 --> 00:20.719
So why on earth
would she steal from us?

00:20.721 --> 00:22.287
I needed the money.

00:22.289 --> 00:24.523
Man: She pays to park her car
in the lot.

00:24.525 --> 00:26.025
What happened?

00:26.027 --> 00:27.726
Reports of an altercation.
That's all I know.

00:30.364 --> 00:32.731
Juliette: Almost done.

00:32.733 --> 00:35.300
You're so good.

00:35.302 --> 00:37.503
There you go.
Mama got you all clean.

00:37.505 --> 00:39.138
All clean.

00:40.141 --> 00:40.873
Yeah.

00:40.875 --> 00:42.875
Aww. Sweet girl.

00:42.877 --> 00:44.176
Good job.

00:44.178 --> 00:46.578
Okeydoke.

00:46.580 --> 00:48.647
Mm!

00:48.649 --> 00:51.383
Okay, well, that's all the time
we get today.

00:51.385 --> 00:52.418
Ohh.

00:52.420 --> 00:53.852
Okay.

00:53.854 --> 00:55.654
Mama's got to say goodbye.

00:55.656 --> 00:57.923
But I'll see you soon.

00:57.925 --> 00:59.825
Thanks, em.
Of course.

00:59.827 --> 01:01.193
Appreciate it.

01:01.195 --> 01:02.895
See you
in a couple days, okay?

01:02.897 --> 01:04.830
Okay.
Say, "bye, mama." bye.

01:04.832 --> 01:06.398
Bye-bye!

01:06.400 --> 01:08.100
Mm.

01:08.102 --> 01:09.368
How do you feel?

01:09.370 --> 01:11.070
Sad to see her go.

01:12.406 --> 01:14.840
But other than that,
I feel really good.

01:14.842 --> 01:16.108
<i> Really</i> good.

01:16.110 --> 01:18.410
Different,
but in a good way.

01:18.412 --> 01:20.279
I'm glad to hear that.

01:20.281 --> 01:23.282
Because I think
you're ready to go home.

01:23.284 --> 01:26.218
[ sighs ]
me too.

01:26.220 --> 01:28.921
[ exhales sharply ]

01:28.923 --> 01:30.622
Deacon: By now,
I'm sure everybody's heard

01:30.624 --> 01:31.957
About vita's disappearance.

01:31.959 --> 01:33.225
[ inhales deeply ]

01:33.227 --> 01:35.127
It's, uh, unfortunate

01:35.129 --> 01:37.229
How everything played out
for her here,

01:37.231 --> 01:40.899
But the police are on it.

01:40.901 --> 01:43.702
Right now all we can do is just
hope and pray that she's okay.

01:43.704 --> 01:46.538
On a brighter note...

01:46.540 --> 01:48.607
As you have seen,

01:48.609 --> 01:52.544
That riff bell show
put this place on the map quick.

01:52.546 --> 01:54.413
Seems like everybody
wants to play here now,

01:54.415 --> 01:56.815
Which means this place
is gonna be packed again,

01:56.817 --> 01:57.816
[ door opens ]
so I want to make sure
everybody's --

01:57.818 --> 01:59.618
Hold on one second, guys.

01:59.620 --> 02:00.452
Hey.
Hey.

02:00.454 --> 02:01.620
What are you doing here?

02:01.622 --> 02:03.122
I just came to grab
my dad's sport coat.

02:03.124 --> 02:04.156
I thought I saw it
in his office.

02:04.158 --> 02:05.557
Oh, all right.
Everything all right?

02:05.559 --> 02:08.293
'cause, uh, he didn't show
for the staff meeting.

02:08.295 --> 02:11.130
Oh. He said he was
taking the morning off.

02:11.132 --> 02:14.299
It's his 15-year anniversary
for being sober today.

02:14.301 --> 02:16.401
[ chuckles ]
that's a big milestone, yeah.

02:16.403 --> 02:18.937
You know, 15 years ago,
I got my dad back.

02:18.939 --> 02:21.006
Mm.
Well, I got to run.

02:21.008 --> 02:23.108
I'm going to be giving him
a cake at the west-end meeting.

02:23.110 --> 02:25.177
[ chuckles ]
that is very sweet.

02:25.179 --> 02:27.246
You know, I'm surprised
he didn't tell me about this.

02:27.248 --> 02:29.181
I'm sure
it just slipped his mind.

02:31.785 --> 02:34.119
<i> Hey. It's vita.</i>
<i> You know what to do.</i>
[<i> beep</i> ]

02:34.121 --> 02:36.188
Hey, vita.
It's rayna -- again.

02:36.190 --> 02:38.524
Um...Please call me.

02:38.526 --> 02:41.160
Let me know you're okay.
Just reach out to me.

02:41.162 --> 02:42.528
All right. Bye.

02:42.530 --> 02:44.530
Ray, you have to stop.

02:44.532 --> 02:45.697
What happened
is not your fault.

02:45.699 --> 02:47.132
There was nothing
you could have done.

02:47.134 --> 02:49.601
I just -- I wish I could have
helped her somehow.

02:49.603 --> 02:51.470
And that detective does not
return my phone calls.

02:51.472 --> 02:53.839
Well, right now, we just need
to let them do their jobs.

02:53.841 --> 02:56.808
Are they doing their jobs?
I don't know, ray,
but we need to be doing<i> ours.</i>

02:56.810 --> 02:58.944
This is a big day. We got to
get our heads in the game.

02:58.946 --> 03:00.279
I'm in it.
I'm in it.

03:00.281 --> 03:02.314
Are we all set for
layla's showcase? Looks good.

03:02.316 --> 03:03.949
Every programmer
that we invited confirmed,

03:03.951 --> 03:05.384
So we're covered
for country radio.

03:05.386 --> 03:07.719
Great. Did we hear
from lady a?

03:07.721 --> 03:10.055
'cause it'd be so great to
tell these guys this afternoon

03:10.057 --> 03:11.690
That we've got layla booked
on a major tour.

03:11.692 --> 03:13.225
I spoke to their people
this morning.

03:13.227 --> 03:14.793
They want to go with someone
better known.

03:14.795 --> 03:15.661
Well...
Yeah.

03:15.663 --> 03:16.862
...It was worth a shot.

03:16.864 --> 03:18.864
And I talked to autumn chase,
and I said,

03:18.866 --> 03:21.200
"hey, come on by this afternoon
if you want to."

03:21.202 --> 03:22.301
Layla would be
a great fit for autumn.

03:22.303 --> 03:23.702
Wouldn't she, though?
Yeah.

03:23.704 --> 03:27.673
Look, I really believe if we can
get this album on the radio,

03:27.675 --> 03:30.475
We will change people's
perception of layla grant.

03:31.478 --> 03:32.978
[ sighs ]

03:32.980 --> 03:35.380
I swear I'm not usually
this much of a basket case.

03:35.382 --> 03:37.883
I just only have three songs
to impress these people.

03:37.885 --> 03:39.518
I just wanted to make sure
I got the right mix.

03:39.520 --> 03:41.320
You don't have to worry.
You're gonna blow them away.

03:41.322 --> 03:43.155
[ door opens ]

03:43.157 --> 03:45.557
Oh. Sorry. I didn't realize
anyone was back here.

03:45.559 --> 03:47.025
That's all right.
We're all done.

03:47.027 --> 03:49.161
Avery was just vetting my
set list for my showcase today.

03:49.163 --> 03:50.729
Oh, yeah,
I heard about that.

03:50.731 --> 03:52.331
Yeah. Knock 'em dead.
Thanks.

03:52.333 --> 03:54.566
Have they scheduled
the exes' showcase yet?

03:54.568 --> 03:56.668
No, we still got a bit of time
before the album launches,

03:56.670 --> 03:58.670
But, uh, bucky's got us playing
a few shows here and there

03:58.672 --> 04:00.372
To tighten things up.

04:00.374 --> 04:02.741
We're playing the bluebird
tonight, if you want to come.

04:02.743 --> 04:03.942
Will's gonna be there.
Really?

04:03.944 --> 04:05.043
Yeah.
What about you?

04:05.045 --> 04:06.612
Yeah, me too.

04:06.614 --> 04:09.014
Okay. Well, if everyone's going,
sure. I'd love to.

04:09.016 --> 04:11.116
Awesome.
Cool.

04:11.118 --> 04:12.684
I guess I'll see you
tonight, then.

04:12.686 --> 04:13.585
All right.

04:14.688 --> 04:17.022
Layla, good luck today.

04:17.024 --> 04:18.123
Thanks.

04:23.864 --> 04:28.467
¶ happy birthday,
dear frankie ¶
¶ happy birthday,
dear dad ¶

04:28.469 --> 04:32.404
¶ happy birthday to you ¶

04:32.406 --> 04:35.474
¶ keep coming back ¶

04:35.476 --> 04:37.009
[ applause ]

04:39.546 --> 04:41.246
Thank you, all.
Thanks.

04:41.248 --> 04:44.549
It's been a while since I've
been the subject of applause.

04:44.551 --> 04:46.718
I've been feeling
a little overshadowed lately,

04:46.720 --> 04:48.987
And...This is nice.

04:51.458 --> 04:53.792
Anyway, I don't want
to go on about it.

04:53.794 --> 04:56.395
I'll just tell you
how grateful I am to be here

04:56.397 --> 04:59.665
And to have my daughter
by my side.

04:59.667 --> 05:01.867
[ applause ]

05:09.610 --> 05:11.310
[ door opens ]

05:11.312 --> 05:12.110
Hey!
Hey.

05:12.112 --> 05:13.578
Long time, will.

05:13.580 --> 05:15.280
Yeah. I appreciate you making
the time to meet with me.

05:15.282 --> 05:17.149
I know you're busy
getting ready for your tour.

05:17.151 --> 05:19.017
Oh, no, I'm happy to.
Happy to.

05:19.019 --> 05:21.486
So, uh, what can I do for you?
Have a seat.

05:21.488 --> 05:25.757
Well, after taking
a little break from performing,

05:25.759 --> 05:27.926
I've decided to start
making music again.

05:27.928 --> 05:29.294
Glad to hear it.

05:29.296 --> 05:30.495
Yeah, I'm gonna
produce my own record

05:30.497 --> 05:32.531
As an independent artist.

05:32.533 --> 05:33.932
You know what --
that's as viable

05:33.934 --> 05:35.634
As any other platform
these days.

05:35.636 --> 05:37.035
It's come a long way

05:37.037 --> 05:38.804
From [chuckling] selling cds
from your trunk.

05:38.806 --> 05:40.939
Yeah, sure has.

05:40.941 --> 05:45.277
So, I was wondering if, um...
If you might consider...

05:45.279 --> 05:48.113
Taking the hold off those songs
I wrote with kevin

05:48.115 --> 05:50.482
So I could release them
myself.

05:50.484 --> 05:51.717
[ cellphone ringing ]

05:53.554 --> 05:55.721
You know what? I'm sorry, will.
I got to take this.

05:55.723 --> 05:57.856
You mind stepping out
for a second?

05:57.858 --> 05:58.890
[ door opens ]
yeah. Sure.

05:58.892 --> 06:01.526
Sorry.
I won't be a minute.

06:01.528 --> 06:02.794
Hey, son.

06:02.796 --> 06:04.062
Hey, dad.

06:04.064 --> 06:06.198
How you doing?
Nice to hear your voice.

06:06.200 --> 06:08.667
Yeah. Listen,
I need something from you.

06:08.669 --> 06:11.636
I need you to sign
a parental-consent waiver.

06:11.638 --> 06:13.105
I'm joining the army.

06:15.509 --> 06:17.376
[ sighs ]

06:22.483 --> 06:24.316
[ bag thuds ]

06:27.654 --> 06:29.554
Home, sweet home.

06:29.556 --> 06:31.556
[ scoffs ]

06:31.558 --> 06:32.991
[ knock on door ]

06:32.993 --> 06:34.159
Patrick: Hello?

06:35.662 --> 06:38.230
Hello...Patrick.

06:38.232 --> 06:39.898
You lurking
outside of my house?

06:39.900 --> 06:41.566
[ chuckles ] you called to say
that you were coming home.

06:41.568 --> 06:44.703
I just -- I wanted
to welcome you back.

06:44.705 --> 06:46.338
Everything okay here,
boss?

06:46.340 --> 06:48.740
Yeah, it's fine.
Thank you.

06:48.742 --> 06:52.077
Look, I hired you to help
spin my absence in the press,

06:52.079 --> 06:54.012
And now that I'm back
and everything's fine,

06:54.014 --> 06:55.180
I don't need your help
anymore.

06:55.182 --> 06:57.215
Yeah, I'm not so sure.

06:57.217 --> 06:58.784
See, while you were gone,
I was fielding offers

06:58.786 --> 07:00.352
For your follow-up
to "shenandoah girl."

07:00.354 --> 07:02.454
And I told you to tell everybody
that I wasn't working.

07:02.456 --> 07:04.122
And I did, but it's true
what they say --

07:04.124 --> 07:06.124
The most powerful word
in the entertainment industry

07:06.126 --> 07:07.692
Is "no."

07:07.694 --> 07:10.462
Spielberg's new film --
there's a great cameo.

07:10.464 --> 07:14.433
Scarlett johansson just
fell out, and now he wants<i> you.</i>

07:14.435 --> 07:16.435
No!

07:16.437 --> 07:17.469
What?

07:17.471 --> 07:18.937
$1 million
for two weeks of work.

07:18.939 --> 07:20.806
It starts shooting in prague
day after tomorrow.

07:20.808 --> 07:22.641
That's incredible.

07:24.578 --> 07:26.111
No. No. No.

07:26.113 --> 07:27.145
I can't do it.
What?

07:27.147 --> 07:28.613
It sounds great.

07:28.615 --> 07:31.316
I need to focus on getting back
into my regular life.

07:31.318 --> 07:32.951
This<i> is</i>
your regular life.

07:32.953 --> 07:34.886
You're juliette barnes.

07:38.425 --> 07:41.493
¶¶

07:48.502 --> 07:50.569
Hey.
Hey!

07:50.571 --> 07:52.604
Congratulations.

07:52.606 --> 07:55.674
I had no idea you were getting
this cake till cash told me.

07:55.676 --> 07:58.310
You're an inspiration to
everyone here -- me most of all.

07:58.312 --> 07:59.845
You talked me
off some ledges, man.

07:59.847 --> 08:01.513
Just doing
what a sponsor does.

08:03.417 --> 08:04.950
Well, listen, why don't you two
let me take you out?

08:04.952 --> 08:05.984
We can celebrate
a little bit.

08:05.986 --> 08:07.118
Yeah.
That'd be awesome.

08:07.120 --> 08:08.286
I mean,
we don't have any plans.

08:08.288 --> 08:11.323
Actually, I was planning
to surprise cash

08:11.325 --> 08:13.091
With a
father/daughter lunch.

08:13.093 --> 08:14.626
Oh.
Ohh!

08:14.628 --> 08:16.127
Well, yeah.

08:16.129 --> 08:17.662
All right.
Y'all have fun.

08:17.664 --> 08:19.064
Bye.

08:21.935 --> 08:23.068
[ sighs ]

08:25.272 --> 08:26.838
How is it?

08:26.840 --> 08:28.473
It's amazing.

08:28.475 --> 08:30.041
Oh, my god.
This script.

08:30.043 --> 08:32.677
It's steven spielberg.
It's a dream role.

08:32.679 --> 08:34.145
But...?

08:34.147 --> 08:36.281
I wasn't even considering
going back to work,

08:36.283 --> 08:37.816
Let alone acting.

08:37.818 --> 08:39.618
So you're gonna pass?

08:39.620 --> 08:41.453
I don't know.

08:41.455 --> 08:44.523
You know avery only lets me
see her three hours a week,

08:44.525 --> 08:47.158
So it's not like
I get to see her very often.

08:47.160 --> 08:49.027
If I knew I could spend
more time with her,

08:49.029 --> 08:50.795
It'd be a no-brainer.

08:50.797 --> 08:53.064
Well, do you want me
to talk to him?

08:53.066 --> 08:54.499
See if he'd give you
more time?

08:54.501 --> 08:58.403
You know what? I can't have you
be the go-between forever.

08:58.405 --> 09:00.238
I'll talk to him myself.

09:00.240 --> 09:04.743
[ "mess worth making" plays ]

09:04.745 --> 09:06.878
¶ sometimes we're dancin'
in the kitchen ¶

09:06.880 --> 09:09.147
¶ sometimes
I'm throwin' dinner plates ¶

09:09.149 --> 09:11.216
¶ sometimes
the world stands still ¶

09:11.218 --> 09:13.051
I got to admit, rayna,

09:13.053 --> 09:15.186
I was surprised
when you signed her.

09:15.188 --> 09:16.888
Layla grant comes
with some baggage.

09:16.890 --> 09:18.056
Look,
she's 21 years old.

09:18.058 --> 09:19.558
Didn't you ever do
anything embarrassing

09:19.560 --> 09:21.359
When you were that age?
Well, yeah, but it's --

09:21.361 --> 09:23.728
Only difference is, we got to
make our mistakes in private.

09:23.730 --> 09:25.363
True.

09:25.365 --> 09:27.532
So, how does one transition
from reality-show star

09:27.534 --> 09:29.067
To country radio?

09:29.069 --> 09:30.168
[ chuckles ]
come on, mark.

09:30.170 --> 09:31.937
Carrie didn't have
any trouble doing it.

09:31.939 --> 09:34.706
Look, I know it's not easy
to take me seriously,

09:34.708 --> 09:37.509
But I don't regret
anything that I've done.

09:37.511 --> 09:43.014
Every step and every misstep
has led me to right here.

09:43.016 --> 09:45.684
So, I'm not perfect,
but I don't really think

09:45.686 --> 09:48.520
That perfect makes
for a very good song.

09:48.522 --> 09:50.755
[ chuckles ]
well said, layla.

09:50.757 --> 09:52.057
Thanks for having me.
Oh. Excuse me.

09:52.059 --> 09:53.858
Autumn!
Hey, girl!
[ chuckles ]

09:53.860 --> 09:56.094
Thanks for coming!
Oh!

09:56.096 --> 09:58.096
How could I miss it
after that pitch you gave me?

09:58.098 --> 09:59.764
Oh, you are gonna
love layla.

09:59.766 --> 10:01.099
I can't wait.

10:01.101 --> 10:02.300
Come on. Let's go.

10:02.302 --> 10:04.869
Oh, my god.
That's autumn chase.

10:04.871 --> 10:07.105
Indeed it is.

10:07.107 --> 10:09.207
Rayna heard she was looking
for a opening act,

10:09.209 --> 10:10.875
So we asked to come down
and have a look.

10:12.212 --> 10:14.012
This is your chance, kiddo.
You ready?

10:18.118 --> 10:19.718
You want to run
"I'm comin' over"?

10:19.720 --> 10:21.453
Yeah. Let's do it.

10:21.455 --> 10:23.154
Hey, man.
H-how'd it go with luke?

10:23.156 --> 10:24.422
He take the hold
off your songs?

10:24.424 --> 10:27.125
He sent me out in the middle
of my pitch to take a call,

10:27.127 --> 10:29.761
And I sat in the lobby
until he blew past me,

10:29.763 --> 10:31.262
Told me
he'd get back to me.

10:31.264 --> 10:32.397
Mm.

10:32.399 --> 10:34.265
[ sighs ]

10:34.267 --> 10:36.434
How am I gonna release
my own record without any songs?

10:36.436 --> 10:38.236
You just
got to write more.

10:38.238 --> 10:41.272
Please. I wrote<i> one</i> song
on my own and then nothing.

10:41.274 --> 10:43.575
I mean...

10:43.577 --> 10:46.311
The only real success I've had
is writing with somebody else.

10:46.313 --> 10:47.746
Hmm.

10:47.748 --> 10:49.781
If only you knew more people
to write songs with.

10:49.783 --> 10:51.182
I know, right?

10:51.184 --> 10:53.151
Like his cma award-winning
songwriter friend

10:53.153 --> 10:54.452
Who is also his roommate?

10:54.454 --> 10:55.987
Or an incredibly talented
poet

10:55.989 --> 10:57.956
Who just finished co-writing
her own record.

10:57.958 --> 10:59.190
Really? You guys would be
willing to help?

10:59.192 --> 11:00.258
Of course, man.
Yeah.

11:00.260 --> 11:01.960
We just got to find
the right time

11:01.962 --> 11:02.994
And all sit down
together.

11:02.996 --> 11:05.363
[ sighs ]
how about right now?

11:05.365 --> 11:07.198
We got to nail down
the set for the bluebird.

11:07.200 --> 11:09.167
Okay. Um,
maybe tomorrow, then.

11:09.169 --> 11:10.769
Well, tomorrow,
we're headed to birmingham

11:10.771 --> 11:12.170
And then mobile
the day after.

11:12.172 --> 11:13.638
Yeah, but there'll
definitely be time

11:13.640 --> 11:14.906
At the end of the week,
when we're back.

11:16.443 --> 11:18.977
Yeah. Sure.
Whatever works.

11:18.979 --> 11:21.279
You know there<i> is</i>
another songwriter
who lives here, right?

11:32.693 --> 11:34.125
You bring the waiver?

11:34.127 --> 11:35.393
No. I didn't.

11:35.395 --> 11:36.861
Well, what are you
doing here?

11:36.863 --> 11:38.363
I came to talk
some sense into you.

11:38.365 --> 11:40.231
Son, this whole thing
has gone way too far --

11:40.233 --> 11:42.067
You living
all the way out here,

11:42.069 --> 11:43.702
Not returning
my texts or calls,

11:43.704 --> 11:45.370
And now you want to join
the army?

11:45.372 --> 11:46.504
It's enough!

11:46.506 --> 11:48.239
Yeah, granddad predicted
you wouldn't sign.

11:48.241 --> 11:49.474
Well, that might be
the first thing

11:49.476 --> 11:51.176
Sarge has gotten right
about me in years.

11:51.178 --> 11:52.844
Whatever.
It doesn't matter.

11:52.846 --> 11:55.213
I'm prepping for the ged,
and I'll be 18 in 3 months.

11:55.215 --> 11:56.648
What's that
supposed to mean?

11:56.650 --> 11:59.584
It means I'll enlist eventually,
whether you like it or not.

12:01.722 --> 12:03.955
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I have some chores to do.

12:06.593 --> 12:08.159
[ engine starts ]

12:13.433 --> 12:15.433
But, I mean,
it's autumn chase, but --

12:15.435 --> 12:17.869
[ sighs ] maybe I should
just change set list.

12:17.871 --> 12:20.004
Look, I know
this is a huge opportunity,

12:20.006 --> 12:22.006
But you can't
get rattled, okay?

12:22.008 --> 12:23.708
[ sighs ]
you're right.

12:23.710 --> 12:26.111
I just -- I -- I don't want
to blow it, you know?

12:26.113 --> 12:27.278
[ knock on door ]
listen to me.

12:27.280 --> 12:29.748
You are an amazing artist
with a giant voice

12:29.750 --> 12:30.949
And something to say.

12:30.951 --> 12:33.585
All you have to do
is open your mouth and sing.

12:34.554 --> 12:36.588
Okay.

12:36.590 --> 12:38.857
Thanks
for talking me down.

12:38.859 --> 12:40.492
You know
you can call me anytime.

12:44.064 --> 12:45.296
Bye.

12:47.567 --> 12:48.700
Hi.

12:54.941 --> 12:56.941
What are you
doing here?

12:56.943 --> 12:58.710
I-I thought you were still
in treatment.

12:58.712 --> 13:00.578
I<i> was.</i>
I checked out this morning.

13:00.580 --> 13:02.547
You should have
called first.

13:02.549 --> 13:04.282
I know.
I wanted to call.

13:04.284 --> 13:06.184
I just was afraid
that you weren't gonna answer.

13:07.621 --> 13:12.657
Look, I know that so much
has happened between us...

13:12.659 --> 13:15.426
And a lot that might
never be resolved.

13:15.428 --> 13:16.861
You're right about that.

13:18.565 --> 13:21.800
This isn't about that, though.
This is about cadence.

13:21.802 --> 13:23.134
And now that I'm home,

13:23.136 --> 13:25.570
I was wondering if I could spend
more time with her.

13:25.572 --> 13:28.173
[ school bell rings ]

13:28.175 --> 13:30.008
I'm sorry,
but the answer is no.

13:33.146 --> 13:38.416
Avery, I know that I've
caused you so much pain,

13:38.418 --> 13:40.618
And I've let<i> you</i> down...
[ sighs ]

13:40.620 --> 13:43.254
...And I let<i> her</i> down,
and I regret it every day.

13:43.256 --> 13:46.024
But I have done so much

13:46.026 --> 13:49.627
To overcome my addictions
and my postpartum,

13:49.629 --> 13:51.529
And I'm so much better.

13:51.531 --> 13:52.997
I promise you.

13:52.999 --> 13:55.333
Look,
I'm happy to hear that.

13:55.335 --> 13:57.035
I really am.

13:57.037 --> 14:00.738
But that all took place
in a protected environment,

14:00.740 --> 14:04.409
And here you are,
the first day out.

14:06.780 --> 14:08.513
I can't trust it.

14:14.120 --> 14:15.353
Okay.

14:15.355 --> 14:19.123
¶ hell, I could write the book ¶

14:19.125 --> 14:24.729
¶ ooh, ooh, ooh ¶
¶ but I won't
give it all away ¶

14:24.731 --> 14:30.101
¶ ooh, ooh ¶
¶ everybody knows
a good heartbreak ¶

14:33.173 --> 14:36.708
¶ oh, I know ¶

14:36.710 --> 14:39.544
¶ how the story goes down ¶

14:39.546 --> 14:42.046
¶ I've told it ¶

14:42.048 --> 14:44.482
¶ about a hundred times now ¶

14:44.484 --> 14:48.052
¶ you're my darkest
desperation ¶

14:48.054 --> 14:50.488
¶ worst kind of creation ¶

14:50.490 --> 14:54.659
¶ even though I know
the story don't end good ¶

14:54.661 --> 14:58.329
¶ hell, I could write the book ¶

15:01.701 --> 15:06.104
¶ oh, I, oh, I ¶

15:06.106 --> 15:09.274
¶ I could write the book ¶

15:09.276 --> 15:12.577
[ cheers and applause ]

15:19.519 --> 15:21.019
Oh, that was great.

15:21.021 --> 15:23.721
Wasn't that fantastic?

15:23.723 --> 15:25.957
[ cheers and applause ]
thank y'all so much for coming.

15:25.959 --> 15:27.392
I am really looking forward

15:27.394 --> 15:30.028
To a very long
and beautiful relationship

15:30.030 --> 15:33.598
Between this stunning artist
and country radio.

15:33.600 --> 15:35.199
Thank you.

15:35.201 --> 15:36.868
And, uh, we got
lots of layla merch over there,

15:36.870 --> 15:38.102
So please help yourselves.

15:38.104 --> 15:39.971
[ indistinct conversations ]

15:42.876 --> 15:44.609
Well, you were right,
rayna.

15:44.611 --> 15:46.711
You most definitely
did not oversell.

15:46.713 --> 15:48.479
That was incredible.

15:48.481 --> 15:50.248
That means so much
coming from you. Thank you.

15:50.250 --> 15:51.616
It's just the truth.

15:51.618 --> 15:53.051
Ms. Jaymes.
Yeah?

15:53.053 --> 15:54.919
A detective from nashville p.D.
Is on the phone for you.

15:54.921 --> 15:57.255
Oh. Um, can y'all excuse me
for a second?

15:57.257 --> 15:59.157
Of course.
Thank you.

15:59.159 --> 16:00.425
So, layla...
[ chuckles ]
yes.

16:00.427 --> 16:01.726
...Tell me something --

16:01.728 --> 16:05.129
How in the world
did you get so wise so young?

16:05.131 --> 16:07.332
That is
a very long story.
Yeah?

16:07.334 --> 16:09.000
Maybe you and I
can hit up adele's later

16:09.002 --> 16:10.335
And you can tell me
all about it.

16:10.337 --> 16:12.437
Yes, absolutely.
Cool.

16:12.439 --> 16:13.504
Oh. [ sighs ]

16:13.506 --> 16:15.073
I actually did
tell some friends

16:15.075 --> 16:16.407
I would go see them
at the bluebird,

16:16.409 --> 16:18.076
But I'm sure they'll understand
if I cancel.

16:18.078 --> 16:19.644
Well, I haven't been
to the bluebird in years.

16:19.646 --> 16:20.812
Maybe I could tag along?

16:20.814 --> 16:22.113
That'd be amazing.

16:22.115 --> 16:23.448
Okay, cool.
See you there, then.

16:23.450 --> 16:24.849
Great.

16:27.587 --> 16:29.020
[ sighs ]

16:30.323 --> 16:31.489
[ beep ]

16:31.491 --> 16:33.458
Detective gibbs,
thank you so much

16:33.460 --> 16:35.093
For returning
my phone call.

16:35.095 --> 16:36.627
I don't know
what I can tell you, ms. Jaymes.

16:36.629 --> 16:38.463
The investigation
is ongoing.

16:38.465 --> 16:40.932
Do we have any information
on where vita might be?

16:40.934 --> 16:42.967
Are there any suspects?

16:42.969 --> 16:45.203
Look, I appreciate your
interest, but at this point,

16:45.205 --> 16:46.871
We don't even know
if there<i> was</i> a crime.

16:46.873 --> 16:48.339
What?
Her car was burned out.

16:48.341 --> 16:50.441
Her guitar,
everything was destroyed.

16:50.443 --> 16:53.878
But there was no blood,
no witnesses, no hard evidence,

16:53.880 --> 16:55.813
Which means we have to
look at all the possibilities,

16:55.815 --> 16:57.515
And that takes time.

16:57.517 --> 17:00.151
So, please, ms. Jaymes, allow us
to complete our investigation.

17:00.153 --> 17:02.153
There's nothing more
you can do, okay?

17:02.155 --> 17:03.354
Thank you.

17:09.062 --> 17:10.728
Hey.

17:10.730 --> 17:12.296
How was lunch?

17:12.298 --> 17:13.131
Good.

17:14.367 --> 17:15.533
Good.

17:15.535 --> 17:17.535
Listen,
I was thinking --

17:17.537 --> 17:19.003
Why don't you
play a set tonight --

17:19.005 --> 17:20.371
You know,
open for the clickin' sticks?

17:20.373 --> 17:21.572
Place is gonna be packed.

17:21.574 --> 17:23.741
I'm not sure
my sound's quite the fit

17:23.743 --> 17:25.309
For that hipster crowd.

17:25.311 --> 17:26.711
[ chuckles ]
come on, now, man.

17:26.713 --> 17:29.514
It'd be a great way
to celebrate your birthday,

17:29.516 --> 17:31.916
Make up for me
bumping you earlier in the week.

17:31.918 --> 17:33.885
How generous of you.

17:35.422 --> 17:37.488
You're not still holding
a grudge about that, are you?

17:37.490 --> 17:39.424
Nope.

17:39.426 --> 17:40.825
Then what is it,
frankie?

17:40.827 --> 17:41.993
You know, is it the vita thing
or what?

17:41.995 --> 17:43.327
'cause I couldn't help
but thinking

17:43.329 --> 17:45.196
That some of that stuff
you were talking about today

17:45.198 --> 17:46.731
In that meeting
was directed at me.

17:46.733 --> 17:48.099
Not everything's
about you, deacon.

17:49.436 --> 17:50.501
All right.

17:50.503 --> 17:52.870
So, what time is
this opening slot

17:52.872 --> 17:54.305
I've been given to play?

17:55.341 --> 17:57.542
You go on at 8:00.

17:57.544 --> 17:58.910
Guess I'll see you
at showtime.

17:58.912 --> 18:00.178
All right.

18:03.183 --> 18:05.283
So, tell me
what's going on.

18:05.285 --> 18:07.251
I had that conversation
with avery

18:07.253 --> 18:09.220
About spending more time
with cadence,

18:09.222 --> 18:13.458
And he...
Completely shut me down.

18:13.460 --> 18:18.629
I've spent all this time
and energy and...Effort

18:18.631 --> 18:21.065
Working on myself,
and he still doesn't trust me.

18:21.067 --> 18:24.435
I understand
you're disappointed,

18:24.437 --> 18:27.438
But you have to respect
avery's experience in this.

18:27.440 --> 18:29.474
Give him time. He'll see
the progress you've made.

18:29.476 --> 18:31.142
What am I supposed to do
until then?

18:31.144 --> 18:32.477
What would you
normally do?

18:32.479 --> 18:34.545
Work.

18:34.547 --> 18:38.716
I actually just got an offer
on this really incredible film,

18:38.718 --> 18:39.784
And I'd like to do it.

18:39.786 --> 18:41.285
That's great.
Yeah.

18:41.287 --> 18:42.753
It would mean
that I'd have to spend

18:42.755 --> 18:44.489
Two weeks
away from cadence.

18:44.491 --> 18:46.257
Are you afraid you'll lose
your connection with her?

18:46.259 --> 18:47.225
No. No.

18:47.227 --> 18:48.626
Actually, we've --

18:48.628 --> 18:51.095
We've bonded a lot
over the last few months.

18:51.097 --> 18:52.497
So what's
holding you back?

18:52.499 --> 18:56.000
Even though I'd only be missing
six hours with her,

18:56.002 --> 18:58.136
It's the only six hours
I have.

18:58.138 --> 19:00.938
Then you just have to
ask yourself,

19:00.940 --> 19:03.341
"is this opportunity
worth it?"

19:03.343 --> 19:06.210
[ breathes deeply ]

19:10.283 --> 19:11.349
[ chuckling ]
well.

19:11.351 --> 19:12.450
How long has it been

19:12.452 --> 19:14.152
Since you've been
on real farmland, huh?

19:14.154 --> 19:15.786
Yeah. I'll cut
right to it, sarge.

19:15.788 --> 19:18.156
I know you're responsible
for polluting colt's mind

19:18.158 --> 19:20.424
With all this army nonsense,
but he is<i> my</i> son.

19:20.426 --> 19:21.859
You know,
that's a hell of a description

19:21.861 --> 19:23.995
For a commitment to honor, duty,
and serving your country.

19:23.997 --> 19:25.363
That is not
what I meant.

19:25.365 --> 19:27.265
Everybody knows
I support the troops.

19:27.267 --> 19:30.434
Right.
You'll sing for them.

19:30.436 --> 19:33.104
You just won't let your kid
be one of them.

19:40.647 --> 19:41.712
All right, maybe we, uh,
add a line to the first verse,

19:41.714 --> 19:43.948
Something like,
"after the heart breaks,

19:43.950 --> 19:45.950
It heals
but still aches."

19:45.952 --> 19:47.451
That's perfect.
I love it.

19:47.453 --> 19:48.653
Okay, cool.

19:48.655 --> 19:50.555
All right, let's, uh,
let's take it from the top.

19:50.557 --> 19:51.556
Let's see what we got.

19:51.558 --> 19:54.458
[ cellphone ringing ]

19:54.460 --> 19:56.194
Ugh. Juliette.

19:56.196 --> 19:58.029
Well, you can take it
if you want.

19:58.031 --> 19:59.897
I don't want to,
but I probably should.

19:59.899 --> 20:01.966
I'll just be a minute.

20:05.872 --> 20:07.838
Hello?

20:07.840 --> 20:10.041
Hey. Thanks
for answering.

20:10.043 --> 20:11.842
Yeah. I'm, uh,
sort of the middle of something.

20:11.844 --> 20:13.144
Okay.

20:13.146 --> 20:15.346
Um, I just wanted
to let you know

20:15.348 --> 20:18.015
That I accepted a role
in a movie.

20:18.017 --> 20:20.551
Okay. And you're telling me
this because...?

20:20.553 --> 20:23.187
Because I'm leaving
for new york tomorrow,

20:23.189 --> 20:25.189
And I'm gonna be gone
after that

20:25.191 --> 20:27.091
For two weeks in europe,
filming.

20:27.093 --> 20:28.759
I thought you wanted
more time with cadence.

20:28.761 --> 20:30.695
Now you're telling me
you won't see her for two weeks?

20:30.697 --> 20:32.730
Well, originally,
I was gonna turn the role down

20:32.732 --> 20:35.566
If I could spend more time
with cadence, but, you know...

20:35.568 --> 20:36.934
What? What?

20:36.936 --> 20:38.936
I-I wouldn't give it to you,
so this is somehow on<i> me?</i>

20:38.938 --> 20:40.538
[ scoffs ]
no. That's not
what I'm saying.

20:40.540 --> 20:42.206
I just -- I decided

20:42.208 --> 20:43.975
That this wasn't something
I could pass up.

20:46.346 --> 20:47.745
Is that it?

20:47.747 --> 20:49.347
Actually, no.

20:49.349 --> 20:52.883
Um...I was wondering
if I could see cadence tonight

20:52.885 --> 20:54.051
Since I'm leaving
tomorrow.

20:54.053 --> 20:57.188
I don't know.
I don't know.

20:57.190 --> 20:58.856
I mean,
we -- we have a set schedule,

20:58.858 --> 21:00.925
And, um,
she's been fussy.

21:00.927 --> 21:02.226
That's okay.

21:02.228 --> 21:04.028
That's totally fine.
I can handle that.

21:05.398 --> 21:07.031
[ sighs ]

21:07.033 --> 21:09.100
[ mid-tempo music plays ]

21:11.638 --> 21:12.637
[ door opens ]

21:12.639 --> 21:14.538
[ music stops ]

21:14.540 --> 21:16.474
All right,
where were we?

21:16.476 --> 21:18.409
Just fiddling
with the first verse.

21:18.411 --> 21:19.710
Right. Yeah.

21:19.712 --> 21:21.479
What'd she want?

21:21.481 --> 21:23.547
[ chuckles ] "what<i> doesn't</i>
she want" is more like it.

21:23.549 --> 21:25.283
[ sighs ]

21:25.285 --> 21:27.118
Well, I was
thinking, um --

21:27.120 --> 21:29.387
I mean, first, she just --
she shows up unannounced

21:29.389 --> 21:31.289
And asks for more time
with cadence, right?

21:31.291 --> 21:33.291
Now she calls and says
she's taking a movie

21:33.293 --> 21:34.943
And leaving again tomorrow.
Well, maybe --

21:34.944 --> 21:36.594
Oh, and -- and she wants
to come over tonight

21:36.596 --> 21:37.795
To put cadence to sleep.

21:37.797 --> 21:39.997
And because I feel guilty,
I agreed.

21:39.999 --> 21:42.600
I mean, who knows
if she's even capable?

21:42.602 --> 21:44.568
Okay. I don't want
to think about it right now.

21:44.570 --> 21:47.405
Let's -- let's do this.
Let's just finish this song.

21:47.407 --> 21:49.507
Honestly, man, I d-- I don't
think you're in any state.

21:49.509 --> 21:50.941
No, no, I'm good.
No, we got a good start.

21:50.943 --> 21:53.244
I-I can work on it more.

21:53.246 --> 21:56.080
You go get yourself a beer
and just...

21:57.817 --> 21:59.517
Yeah.

21:59.519 --> 22:01.252
Right.

22:01.254 --> 22:02.653
Okay.

22:04.157 --> 22:05.990
[ sighing ] okay.

22:08.027 --> 22:09.827
[ door opens, closes ]
[ sighs ]

22:09.829 --> 22:11.595
All right.

22:11.597 --> 22:13.097
You have got to be
kidding me.

22:13.099 --> 22:14.598
Autumn chase is
coming here tonight?

22:14.600 --> 22:15.833
Yeah.

22:15.835 --> 22:17.034
She's, like,
one of my biggest idols.

22:17.036 --> 22:18.803
I had "not this time"
on a loop for ages.

22:18.805 --> 22:20.471
So you know all about her.
Can you help me out?

22:20.473 --> 22:22.540
I mean, what do I say?
Be yourself.

22:22.542 --> 22:24.508
I mean, she's heard you sing.
She wants to hang out.

22:24.510 --> 22:26.510
Pretty much means
you got the job already.

22:26.512 --> 22:28.312
And if not, you got
a couple of handsome wingmen

22:28.314 --> 22:29.547
Coming down to help you
seal the deal.

22:29.549 --> 22:30.648
[ cellphone dings ]
[ chuckles ]

22:30.650 --> 22:32.216
Make that
<i> "one</i> handsome wingman."

22:32.218 --> 22:34.051
[ cellphone dings ]
um, avery's not coming
after all.

22:34.053 --> 22:36.020
Says something came up.

22:36.022 --> 22:38.122
Oh. Will's not coming,
either.

22:38.124 --> 22:39.523
He's gonna stay home
and write.

22:39.525 --> 22:41.158
Well, you're gonna have<i> us</i>
standing up there

22:41.160 --> 22:42.293
Smiling at you
from the stage.

22:42.295 --> 22:43.294
You're gonna be great.

22:43.296 --> 22:45.029
Yeah.
Thanks.
Don't worry.

22:45.031 --> 22:46.831
Oh, there she is.
Hey.

22:46.833 --> 22:47.865
Hey, gal.

22:47.867 --> 22:49.300
I'm glad you came.

22:49.302 --> 22:51.001
Autumn, these are my friends
scarlett and gunnar.

22:51.003 --> 22:52.636
They're with
highway 65, too.

22:52.638 --> 22:54.372
It's an honor to meet you.
Real fan.

22:54.374 --> 22:55.840
Yeah, me too.
[ chuckles ]

22:55.842 --> 22:57.675
Thank you so much.
You guys headlining tonight?

22:57.677 --> 22:59.176
Yeah. Yeah.

22:59.178 --> 23:00.678
Uh, speaking of which,
we should probably...

23:00.680 --> 23:02.580
Yep.
It was really great
meeting you.

23:02.582 --> 23:03.647
Likewise.

23:03.649 --> 23:05.015
Good luck.
Thanks.

23:05.017 --> 23:07.485
And just for the record,
layla's awesome.

23:07.487 --> 23:10.855
[ chuckles ]

23:10.857 --> 23:12.289
[ sighs ]

23:14.527 --> 23:15.993
[ sighs ]

23:15.995 --> 23:17.728
Hey, cash?
Hmm?

23:17.730 --> 23:18.929
You seen your dad?

23:18.931 --> 23:21.165
No. What time was he
supposed to go on, again?

23:21.167 --> 23:22.733
[ sighs ]
15 minutes ago.

23:22.735 --> 23:25.269
You were right!
Place is packed!

23:25.271 --> 23:26.704
[ chuckles ]

23:26.706 --> 23:28.406
Yeah, it's packed.
It's sold out.

23:28.408 --> 23:30.174
They've been waiting
for you to play some music.

23:30.176 --> 23:32.410
Now, what happened? You forget
your set time or something?

23:32.412 --> 23:35.513
Where you been?
No. No, I stopped to get
a cup of coffee.

23:35.515 --> 23:37.047
Relax, man.

23:37.049 --> 23:39.216
Look, I just want it to be
another great night, all right?

23:39.218 --> 23:41.085
I intend for it
to be memorable.

23:47.026 --> 23:48.692
So, I hope
you can forgive me,

23:48.694 --> 23:50.928
But I googled you
this afternoon.

23:50.930 --> 23:52.430
[ chuckles ] no.

23:52.432 --> 23:54.131
Please don't hold
any of that stuff against me.

23:54.133 --> 23:55.733
Oh, stop. No.

23:55.735 --> 23:58.803
It turns out you and I actually
have a whole lot in common.

23:58.805 --> 24:01.739
Would you believe<i> my</i> first gig
was on a reality tv show, too?

24:01.741 --> 24:03.040
[ chuckles ]

24:03.042 --> 24:04.809
"star search" --
before your time.

24:04.811 --> 24:06.243
No. I remember that show,
I think.

24:06.245 --> 24:08.145
You think?
[ both laugh ]

24:08.147 --> 24:12.082
Oh, also, you're not the only
harvard girl at this table.

24:12.084 --> 24:13.651
No way.
Mm-hmm.

24:13.653 --> 24:15.953
Harvard elementary,
houston, texas.

24:15.955 --> 24:17.621
[ laughs ]

24:17.623 --> 24:20.491
Oh, and my first boyfriend
also turned out to be gay.

24:20.493 --> 24:21.659
No!
Yeah.

24:21.661 --> 24:23.227
It's like
we're the same person.

24:23.229 --> 24:24.328
[ chuckles ]
yeah.

24:24.330 --> 24:26.063
Welcome to the bluebird.

24:26.065 --> 24:28.933
[ cheers and applause ]
we have a special show
for you tonight.

24:28.935 --> 24:30.501
The act you're about to see

24:30.503 --> 24:32.269
Actually met here
at the bluebird.

24:32.271 --> 24:34.638
Please welcome the exes.

24:34.640 --> 24:36.507
[ cheers and applause ]

24:39.078 --> 24:40.644
Well,
thank y'all so much.

24:42.114 --> 24:46.150
¶ oh, babe ¶

24:46.152 --> 24:51.088
¶ I'm never good
with words to say ¶

24:51.090 --> 24:55.826
¶ I'm not myself
when you're away ¶

24:55.828 --> 24:59.730
¶ and I've had
all that I can take ¶

25:01.801 --> 25:05.836
¶ oh, baby ¶

25:05.838 --> 25:10.474
¶ the moon is
staring back at me ¶

25:10.476 --> 25:15.546
¶ start missing you
and I can't sleep ¶

25:15.548 --> 25:18.549
¶ you are the only thing I see ¶

25:18.551 --> 25:21.285
You know, rayna really has
an eye for talent.

25:21.287 --> 25:23.554
I feel like between you
and these guys,

25:23.556 --> 25:25.990
The future of country music is
right here in this room.

25:25.992 --> 25:27.124
[ chuckles ]

25:27.126 --> 25:28.959
From your lips
to god's ears.

25:31.864 --> 25:34.899
¶ wait for me outside ¶

25:34.901 --> 25:38.903
¶ I'm comin' over ¶

25:40.673 --> 25:44.542
¶ oh, babe ¶

25:44.544 --> 25:49.914
¶ ooh, ooh, ooh ¶

25:53.986 --> 25:55.386
I assumed you left.

25:55.388 --> 25:57.288
I couldn't leave
with the way things are.

25:58.391 --> 26:00.357
You know what you're
getting yourself into here?

26:00.359 --> 26:01.492
Yeah.

26:01.494 --> 26:03.761
But do you really?

26:03.763 --> 26:05.095
I'm honestly asking, colt,

26:05.097 --> 26:07.231
Because when I was
on that uso tour

26:07.233 --> 26:09.733
And we drove over
that ied...

26:09.735 --> 26:13.270
[ sighs ] that fear is something
I'll never forget.

26:13.272 --> 26:15.105
Yeah, well, granddad said
you were on a vip convoy.

26:15.107 --> 26:18.075
Exactly -- whereas<i> you</i> could be
out on the front lines.

26:19.278 --> 26:20.544
You need to understand
something, son.

26:20.546 --> 26:23.213
I'm not fighting you 'cause
I'm trying to control you.

26:23.215 --> 26:25.916
I-I'm doing it
'cause I'm terrified.

26:27.186 --> 26:29.253
I know you might
hate my guts right now,

26:29.255 --> 26:30.554
But I love you so much,

26:30.556 --> 26:33.457
And I don't want you
to get hurt.

26:33.459 --> 26:35.225
[ sighs ]

26:35.227 --> 26:37.328
I might not know
what to expect...

26:40.099 --> 26:42.366
...But I know I found
something I believe in.

26:43.803 --> 26:45.135
Just 'cause
it's gonna be scary

26:45.137 --> 26:46.971
Doesn't mean
I'm not gonna do it.

26:51.544 --> 26:52.977
All right.

26:54.547 --> 26:55.980
Why don't we go inside,

26:55.982 --> 26:58.315
And you can tell me
more about it?

26:59.485 --> 27:00.718
Okay.

27:00.720 --> 27:03.821
[ mid-tempo music plays ]

27:03.823 --> 27:05.422
[ music stops ]

27:05.424 --> 27:08.292
[ scattered applause,
indistinct conversations ]

27:08.294 --> 27:12.162
Hey! Did y'all come here
to listen or talk?

27:12.164 --> 27:14.798
Chatting up like a bunch
of schoolgirls out there.

27:14.800 --> 27:15.966
[ light laughter ]

27:15.968 --> 27:17.167
You think that's funny?

27:17.169 --> 27:18.602
Yeah.
Yeah, a little bit.

27:18.604 --> 27:20.004
I got a hilarious idea.

27:20.006 --> 27:21.271
How about I walk out there

27:21.273 --> 27:23.307
And throw your happy ass
out of my bar?

27:23.309 --> 27:24.308
My god. He's drunk.

27:24.310 --> 27:25.643
[ laughs ]
that would be real funny!

27:25.645 --> 27:27.778
I know. Why don't you
cut on out of here, okay?

27:27.780 --> 27:29.913
I'll break your damn neck.

27:29.915 --> 27:31.448
I'll take care of this.
You go.

27:31.450 --> 27:32.716
This ain't no pool hall.

27:34.253 --> 27:35.986
Not while<i> I'm</i> up here.

27:35.988 --> 27:38.022
Cut his mic.
I tell you what --

27:38.024 --> 27:39.990
Spent all that money
for a damn microphone.

27:39.992 --> 27:41.525
Can't even get the
son of a bitch to work --
hey.
Let's take you down --

27:41.527 --> 27:42.693
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey! You're
gonna spill my drink, brother.

27:42.695 --> 27:43.761
Yeah. I think
you had enough. Let's --

27:43.763 --> 27:45.629
Hey, deacon claybourne,
everybody!

27:45.631 --> 27:47.264
<i> The</i> deacon claybourne!
Let's go!

27:47.266 --> 27:48.966
I ain't done yet.
Yeah, you are.

27:48.968 --> 27:51.769
Who in the hell
you think you are?
Show's over, frankie.

27:55.641 --> 27:57.307
Leave me alone!

27:57.309 --> 27:58.709
Damn it!

27:58.711 --> 28:00.511
Of all damn days.

28:00.513 --> 28:03.814
You give up
15 years of sobriety?!

28:03.816 --> 28:06.216
Today wasn't
my first drink.

28:06.218 --> 28:09.119
I had that a few nights ago
while you were out there

28:09.121 --> 28:11.155
Hamming it up
with your buddies onstage,

28:11.157 --> 28:13.991
Treating me
like a barback.

28:13.993 --> 28:16.160
This used to be<i> my</i> place.

28:16.162 --> 28:17.461
It's still your place,
frankie.

28:17.463 --> 28:19.496
You took it from me.

28:19.498 --> 28:21.331
You took all it was,
turned it into a sideshow.

28:21.333 --> 28:23.801
I didn't<i> take</i> your bar.
I<i> saved</i> your bar, frankie!

28:23.803 --> 28:26.036
You erased me, damn it!

28:27.807 --> 28:29.073
What are you
talking about?

28:30.242 --> 28:32.176
The second you hung that sign
out there

28:32.178 --> 28:33.911
With your dead sister's name
on it.

28:33.913 --> 28:35.312
All right, you watch yourself
right now.

28:35.314 --> 28:37.581
It's all about<i> you.</i>

28:37.583 --> 28:39.083
[ sighs ]

28:39.085 --> 28:41.518
But not anymore.

28:41.520 --> 28:43.353
I'm taking it back.

28:43.355 --> 28:45.089
You ain't going out there
unless you go through me.

28:45.091 --> 28:46.924
[ exhales heavily ]

28:46.926 --> 28:49.393
You ain't made of much.

28:49.395 --> 28:51.328
There's two ways
this is gonna go, frankie.

28:51.330 --> 28:54.531
Both of them involve
you sleeping it off --

28:54.533 --> 28:58.068
Passed out
or knocked out.

28:58.070 --> 28:59.837
[ scoffs ]

29:17.556 --> 29:19.256
[ sighs heavily ]

29:19.258 --> 29:21.625
[ chuckles ]

29:37.910 --> 29:40.410
[ "spinning revolver" plays ]

29:40.412 --> 29:43.113
¶ well, a heart ¶

29:43.115 --> 29:47.317
¶ it's a fragile thing,
hangin' on a string ¶

29:47.319 --> 29:49.586
¶ it don't take much ¶

29:49.588 --> 29:50.988
[ chuckles ]

29:50.990 --> 29:54.057
¶ and a soul ¶

29:54.059 --> 29:58.128
¶ it's a little bit stronger,
takes a little longer ¶

29:58.130 --> 29:59.997
¶ to use it up ¶

30:02.001 --> 30:04.735
Detective gibbs.

30:04.737 --> 30:05.769
I'm rayna jaymes.

30:05.771 --> 30:07.304
Yes. I know.

30:07.306 --> 30:09.139
Look, I don't mean
any disrespect,

30:09.141 --> 30:11.508
But I-I'm just --
I'm feeling like

30:11.510 --> 30:14.011
This vita case
is not a priority for you.

30:14.013 --> 30:15.579
And I don't know
if that's 'cause she's homeless

30:15.581 --> 30:18.916
And she doesn't have
a family advocating for her

30:18.918 --> 30:21.418
And demanding answers.

30:21.420 --> 30:23.787
So that's why I just wanted
to show up in person

30:23.789 --> 30:25.422
And let you know
that<i> I'm</i> advocating for her.

30:26.759 --> 30:28.792
And I want answers.

30:28.794 --> 30:31.161
Let me show you
something.

30:36.602 --> 30:40.137
Stacy richardson,
tameka johnston, michele mcgee.

30:40.139 --> 30:42.439
I have eight open cases
just like vita's

30:42.441 --> 30:44.608
And dozens more
in the cold-case file.

30:44.610 --> 30:46.376
I know every name
and every face,

30:46.378 --> 30:49.179
And believe me --
I want justice for all of them.

30:49.181 --> 30:51.348
The sad truth is,
girls like vita --

30:51.350 --> 30:53.717
They have a tendency
to end up in dicey situations,

30:53.719 --> 30:55.719
And many of them...

30:55.721 --> 30:57.554
They just disappear.

30:57.556 --> 31:00.557
Now, I promise you
I'm not giving up.

31:00.559 --> 31:03.227
But right now, there's not much
either of us can do.

31:03.229 --> 31:04.561
I'm sorry.

31:04.563 --> 31:06.563
[ telephone rings ]
excuse me.

31:06.565 --> 31:08.198
This is detective gibbs.

31:11.170 --> 31:13.670
Thanks again
for letting me do this.

31:13.672 --> 31:16.506
She's, uh, had her bottle
and a bath,

31:16.508 --> 31:19.376
So she just needs
to be put to bed.

31:19.378 --> 31:22.212
Here you go.

31:22.214 --> 31:24.414
Come to mama.
[ cadence fusses ]

31:24.416 --> 31:26.049
Ohh.

31:26.051 --> 31:27.918
Shh, shh.
It's okay.

31:27.920 --> 31:29.052
Here,
maybe I should --

31:29.054 --> 31:31.021
No, it's okay.
I got it.

31:31.023 --> 31:32.322
Don't worry.

31:32.324 --> 31:33.257
Okay.

31:33.259 --> 31:35.893
I'll, uh...
Just be down the hall.

31:38.564 --> 31:40.664
[ shushing ]

31:40.666 --> 31:43.600
Aw, baby,
it's all right.

31:43.602 --> 31:46.737
You want mama
to sing to you, hmm?

31:49.241 --> 31:54.211
¶ why'd I get to be so lucky? ¶

31:54.213 --> 31:58.348
¶ why'd I get to be the one ¶

31:58.350 --> 32:04.888
¶ who gets to breathe again,
feel again, dream again ¶

32:04.890 --> 32:08.091
¶ who gets to move on? ¶

32:08.093 --> 32:13.430
¶ if I could forgive myself ¶

32:13.432 --> 32:18.468
¶ if I could just let go ¶

32:18.470 --> 32:23.440
¶ of all the things
I couldn't change ¶

32:23.442 --> 32:28.045
¶ of all the things
I didn't know ¶

32:28.047 --> 32:32.916
¶ if I could take all the pain ¶

32:32.918 --> 32:37.955
¶ that I brought on you,
I would ¶

32:37.957 --> 32:42.492
¶ I would do anything ¶

32:42.494 --> 32:48.765
¶ if I could forgive myself ¶

32:48.767 --> 32:52.069
[ printer whirring ]

32:52.071 --> 32:53.270
Good morning.

32:53.272 --> 32:55.672
I'm not sure
there's much good about it.

32:55.674 --> 32:58.075
Well...You're alive.

32:58.077 --> 33:01.478
Look, I'm sorry
about last night --

33:01.480 --> 33:05.415
For what I remember,
but mostly for what I<i> don't.</i>

33:05.417 --> 33:07.751
Well, you lived up
to cash's recollection.

33:07.753 --> 33:09.353
[ chuckles ]

33:09.355 --> 33:11.121
You're a mean sob
when you get liquored up.

33:11.123 --> 33:13.523
Listen, whatever nonsense
that I was spouting,

33:13.525 --> 33:14.624
I didn't mean it.

33:14.626 --> 33:16.026
Yeah, you did.

33:16.028 --> 33:17.527
As much as I hate
to admit it,

33:17.529 --> 33:19.329
There's a whole lot of truth
in what you said.

33:19.331 --> 33:21.231
Come on, deacon.
No. No. Listen to me.

33:25.204 --> 33:27.604
I got caught up --

33:27.606 --> 33:29.873
First in trying to pay tribute
to my sister

33:29.875 --> 33:31.875
And then in trying
to make this place

33:31.877 --> 33:33.877
Some kind
of overnight success.

33:33.879 --> 33:36.446
Well, you succeeded --
on both counts.

33:36.448 --> 33:38.181
Not without steamrolling you
in the process.

33:39.518 --> 33:41.018
[ sighing ]
oh, frankie.

33:43.956 --> 33:46.723
Think of all the times
you kept me on the wagon.

33:48.494 --> 33:51.962
I end up being the one
to make you lose 15 years.

33:51.964 --> 33:58.035
I can't let you take the blame
for my actions.

33:58.037 --> 33:59.336
I slipped.

33:59.338 --> 34:03.540
What hurts me the most
is that...

34:03.542 --> 34:05.175
I made a vow to cash

34:05.177 --> 34:08.912
She'd never have to see me
like that again.

34:08.914 --> 34:11.882
I'm not sure...
How to face her now.

34:11.884 --> 34:13.984
Well,
it won't be alone.

34:17.689 --> 34:19.890
After that,
it's just one day at a time.

34:19.892 --> 34:22.893
[ sighs ]

34:22.895 --> 34:24.428
It's all right, brother.

34:31.570 --> 34:32.769
You sure about this?

34:32.771 --> 34:34.104
Yes, sir.

34:39.711 --> 34:41.945
Excuse me. Um...

34:41.947 --> 34:43.447
My son would like
to join the army.

34:43.449 --> 34:45.415
Yes, sir.

34:45.417 --> 34:46.850
Son?

34:49.621 --> 34:51.755
[ indistinct shouting ]
reporter: Ms. Barnes.

34:51.757 --> 34:54.524
You've only done one movie,
and people are talking oscar.

34:54.526 --> 34:56.093
Now you're working
with hollywood royalty.

34:56.095 --> 34:57.094
How does it feel?

34:57.096 --> 34:58.061
Incredible.

34:58.063 --> 35:00.564
I feel so honored
and grateful,

35:00.566 --> 35:02.799
And I just really hope
that I don't let anybody down.

35:02.801 --> 35:04.534
[ chuckles ]
[ indistinct shouting ]

35:04.536 --> 35:06.870
Reporter #2:
Ms. Barnes, you've managed
to stay on top of the world,

35:06.872 --> 35:09.239
Despite having challenges
in your personal life,

35:09.241 --> 35:11.074
Notably
the death of your manager

35:11.076 --> 35:12.642
And the announcement
of your divorce.

35:12.644 --> 35:14.144
How do you manage
to pull it off,

35:14.146 --> 35:15.846
Especially now,
being a single mom?

35:23.322 --> 35:25.789
I haven't been doing well.

35:25.791 --> 35:27.757
And that's the truth.

35:27.759 --> 35:29.960
I've been suffering
from postpartum depression

35:29.962 --> 35:32.629
Since my daughter
was born.

35:32.631 --> 35:34.664
And I've been treatment
for the past two months,

35:34.666 --> 35:36.133
And I got out yesterday.

35:36.135 --> 35:39.236
I was headed down a dark path,

35:39.238 --> 35:41.171
And it cost me my marriage

35:41.173 --> 35:42.739
And my relationship
with my daughter

35:42.741 --> 35:44.741
And nearly took my life.

35:46.111 --> 35:47.277
I apologize.

35:47.279 --> 35:49.646
I shouldn't have signed on
to do this movie.

35:51.416 --> 35:53.450
I need to be with my daughter
right now.

35:53.452 --> 35:55.018
[ indistinct shouting ]

36:07.833 --> 36:09.032
Hey, hold up a second.

36:10.869 --> 36:13.603
I wasn't gonna say anything
inside, but, um...

36:13.605 --> 36:17.040
It feels strange as a father
to be learning from your son.

36:17.042 --> 36:20.043
And, uh...
[inhales deeply]

36:20.045 --> 36:22.879
I just want you to know
I'm -- I'm real proud of you.

36:28.554 --> 36:30.387
Thanks, dad.

36:38.130 --> 36:40.063
Hey!
Hey, there she is!

36:40.065 --> 36:41.298
Oh! Good to see you,
honey.

36:41.300 --> 36:42.699
You, too.
Y'all have a seat.

36:42.701 --> 36:45.001
Hey, thanks again for everything
you did for me yesterday.

36:45.003 --> 36:46.536
You did
all the heavy lifting.

36:46.538 --> 36:47.971
You were incredible.
Wasn't she?

36:47.973 --> 36:49.306
Oh, yeah.
And I really think

36:49.308 --> 36:51.508
We will have the full support
of country radio.

36:51.510 --> 36:53.243
Hear that?
You're on your way!

36:53.245 --> 36:55.045
Um, so,
any word from autumn?

36:55.047 --> 36:57.314
We hung out last night,
and we totally clicked.

36:57.316 --> 37:00.183
Yes, I did talk to her,
and she loved you.

37:00.185 --> 37:01.885
She was so impressed
with you.

37:01.887 --> 37:03.820
Um...

37:03.822 --> 37:05.822
I do have
a bit of bad news.

37:08.227 --> 37:09.826
What do you mean,
she picked us?

37:09.828 --> 37:11.228
What are you
not following here?

37:11.230 --> 37:13.563
You're gonna open
for autumn chase on tour.

37:13.565 --> 37:14.397
[ scoffs ]

37:14.399 --> 37:15.832
But she came
to see layla.

37:15.834 --> 37:17.701
Must have blown her away
last night at the bluebird.

37:17.703 --> 37:20.570
Only reason she was at
the bluebird was to see layla.

37:20.572 --> 37:21.771
What'd rayna say?

37:21.773 --> 37:23.106
She's thrilled.

37:23.108 --> 37:25.609
I mean, this is huge
for the exes<i> and</i> highway 65.

37:25.611 --> 37:27.177
So maybe the two of you

37:27.179 --> 37:29.012
Should start looking
a little happier about this.

37:29.014 --> 37:30.447
[ chuckling ]
no, I mean, we're happy.

37:30.449 --> 37:32.449
It's just surprising.

37:32.451 --> 37:34.017
I mean,
how long before we start?

37:34.019 --> 37:35.118
Buses leave
in three days.

37:35.120 --> 37:36.086
Three days?
That soon?

37:36.088 --> 37:37.754
Mm-hmm.
So start packing.

37:37.756 --> 37:41.191
The exes are officially
in the big leagues.

37:42.227 --> 37:42.959
[ chuckles ]

37:42.961 --> 37:44.160
[ chuckles ]

37:47.032 --> 37:49.532
[ sighs ] my name's frankie.

37:49.534 --> 37:50.567
And I'm an alcoholic.

37:50.569 --> 37:53.737
All: Hi, frankie.

37:53.739 --> 37:56.306
I got one day sober.

37:56.308 --> 37:58.108
And, uh...
[ sniffles ]

37:58.110 --> 38:01.144
After 15 years,
that's kind of humbling to say.

38:03.081 --> 38:05.749
But a good buddy of mine
reminded me

38:05.751 --> 38:08.885
This is a daily battle.

38:08.887 --> 38:11.821
And thanks to him and...

38:11.823 --> 38:16.092
My daughter and my lord...

38:16.094 --> 38:18.094
Uh [sniffles]

38:18.096 --> 38:20.063
...I'm winning today.

38:29.808 --> 38:30.907
[ door opens ]

38:30.909 --> 38:32.575
We got to talk.

38:32.577 --> 38:34.010
I tried to stop him.
It's all right, christel.
I got it.

38:35.314 --> 38:37.113
Sorry. I-I should have
called you back.

38:37.115 --> 38:39.416
I had some important stuff
I had to tend to yesterday,

38:39.418 --> 38:40.450
And it slipped my mind.

38:40.452 --> 38:42.752
I get it.

38:42.754 --> 38:44.988
I'm not a priority --
to you or anyone else.

38:44.990 --> 38:47.424
Now, hold on a second.
You just asked me yesterday.

38:47.426 --> 38:49.826
Well, today I'm not asking,
I'm demanding.

38:49.828 --> 38:51.294
I want my songs back.

38:51.296 --> 38:52.629
I worked my ass off
on them,

38:52.631 --> 38:54.364
And just because you dropped me
from your label

38:54.366 --> 38:55.832
Doesn't mean
I don't get to record them.

38:55.834 --> 38:58.968
[ inhales deeply ]

38:58.970 --> 39:00.837
All right, will,
I'll, uh...

39:00.839 --> 39:03.039
I'll take the hold
off your songs.

39:03.041 --> 39:04.307
Seriously?

39:04.309 --> 39:05.809
Yeah, but before I do,

39:05.811 --> 39:08.378
There's something
I'd like you to consider.

39:08.380 --> 39:12.849
I dropped you when I did
'cause I was afraid.

39:12.851 --> 39:15.785
Afraid nashville wouldn't accept
a -- a gay country artist.

39:15.787 --> 39:18.722
Hell, I was afraid it might even
hurt my own career.

39:18.724 --> 39:20.323
But I've come to realize

39:20.325 --> 39:25.662
That just 'cause
something's hard or scary...

39:25.664 --> 39:27.964
Doesn't mean
you shouldn't do it --

39:27.966 --> 39:31.234
Especially if it's something
you believe in.

39:31.236 --> 39:32.936
And I believe in you.

39:34.339 --> 39:36.139
What exactly
are you saying?

39:36.141 --> 39:38.174
That I'm sorry.

39:38.176 --> 39:39.976
And that I'd like you
to come back

39:39.978 --> 39:41.177
To wheelin' dealin' records,

39:41.179 --> 39:42.645
Let<i> me</i>
put out your album,

39:42.647 --> 39:45.815
Like I should have done
the first time around.

39:45.817 --> 39:46.750
What do you say?

39:48.353 --> 39:50.086
You bet.

39:57.996 --> 39:59.062
Hey, there.

39:59.064 --> 40:00.897
Hey. How you doing?

40:00.899 --> 40:02.565
I'm a little beat.

40:02.567 --> 40:04.033
Yeah, I bet.

40:04.035 --> 40:05.535
Long night,
early morning.

40:05.537 --> 40:06.636
Aw.

40:08.507 --> 40:10.440
I missed you last night.
I miss you, too.

40:10.442 --> 40:12.509
How'd your meeting go
with frankie this morning?

40:12.511 --> 40:14.344
It was hard, you know?

40:15.781 --> 40:17.347
How was<i> your</i> meeting?

40:17.349 --> 40:18.081
It was good.

40:18.083 --> 40:19.349
I mean, you know,

40:19.351 --> 40:22.519
I've got country radio ready
to support layla grant.

40:22.521 --> 40:24.421
I got the exes on tour
with autumn chase.
[ chuckles ]

40:24.423 --> 40:27.123
It's been a great couple days
for highway 65.

40:28.527 --> 40:29.926
[ sighs ]

40:29.928 --> 40:31.694
My heart's
not really in it, though.

40:31.696 --> 40:33.363
You thinking about vita?

40:33.365 --> 40:35.732
Yeah.
Me too.

40:35.734 --> 40:39.569
And that visit I had
with the detective last night...

40:39.571 --> 40:41.037
[ sighs ]

40:41.039 --> 40:45.108
You know, he has
a stack of files --

40:45.110 --> 40:49.479
Girls just like vita
and our daughters...

40:49.481 --> 40:53.149
Who just disappeared.

